Description:
Instant Appeal with Perfect Potential
Beyond the distinctive facade of this classic Californian, discover an immaculate interior providing an immediately comfortable family lifestyle along with scope to further enhance and plenty of room to expand (STCA). Previously extended floorplan comprises three double bedrooms (two with BIRs) and central bathroom, light-filled open living/dining area enhanced by an updated kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Other highlights of the home include gas heating, polished timber floors, laundry and separate powder room, plus a surprisingly spacious backyard with established gardens and trees, as well as a tandem double garage via rear ROW. Walking distance to Reynard Street buses and Melville Road trams, local cafes and popular primary schools, it's also close to Coburg Station and renowned shopping precinct along with easy access to Citylink. Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Eclectic Chic Overlooking Merri Creek
A unique Bohemian renovation gives this delightful three bedroom plus studio clinker brick home eclectic appeal, while supremely positioned opposite Merri Creek parklands and trails. The uninterrupted views across the parklands are incredible, but there's so much more on offer, from the native inspired landscaping of the 390m2 preferred corner block (approx), to a prized location situated between Sydney Road's array of shopping, cafes, restaurants, schools, Coburg Pool and the buzzing Preston Market and High Street precinct. The perfect opportunity for first home buyers, young families and investors, with scope to further improve (STCA). This captivating home features open plan living, rustic Japanned floors and an open fireplace, while a sleek CaesarStone kitchen featuring stainless steel appliances and splashbacks add modern glamour.
French doors open to a rustic entertainer's deck and rural inspired gardens with raised beds incorporating a studio providing versatility as an ideal home office or additional bedroom. Two double bedrooms with BIRs, study/third bedroom, central bathroom, reverse cycle heating and cooling, 2500L water tank and potential off street parking via Spring Street complete this unique property where the best of country and urban living coincide.

This one is ready for its next chapter!

Description:
Art Deco Delight
As delightful on the inside as the outside, this Art Deco inspired two bedroom single-fronted red clinker brick residence boasts a coveted corner position on one of Coburg's top tree lined streets. Surrounded by rose gardens, it enjoys a northerly rear aspect and offers potential for future improvements, if desired (subject to council approval). Gorgeous interiors comprise of a light-filled lounge with decorative ceiling panels, plaster-surrounded fireplace and etched glass French doors flowing into a charming fully renovated kitchen, dining space featuring a tapestry brick fireplace. The kitchen has been completely renovated with stainless steel appliances and stone bench top. There are two private bedrooms, with built-in-robes. Modern comforts includes, evaporative cooling, split system air conditioner, period bathroom, polished floorboards, manicured gardens and off-street parking. Walking distance to Coburg North Primary School, Coburg Village, public transport and easy access to the CBD via CityLink.

Eclectic charm, premier lifestyle
Eclectic and with a tremendous sense of retro style this three bedroom plus studio period home presents fuss free living amongst the best Coburg has to offer. Art Deco ceilings and glass panelled doors add architectural interest to a spacious home that features a central dining room flanked by a separate lounge and timber topped kitchen. Boasting Nicholson Street trams, cafes, bustling Sydney Road, Merri Creek trails and schools walking distance.

Description:
Federation Prize with Position and Potential
Beyond the gorgeous facade of this double-fronted period home, discover an inviting interior offering a lifestyle/investment of immediate comfort and unbeatable convenience along with plenty of scope to further enhance. Retaining all its original allure, the home's inviting interior comprises three spacious bedrooms and period-inspired bathroom, elegant lounge and adjoining kitchen/meals area with Falcon oven, timber cabinetry and breakfast bar. Just north of Brunswick's border with trams at the end of the street, it's also walking distance to Moreland Station, local schools, as well as endless cafes and restaurants, boutique shops and major supermarkets. Description:
Private And Prestigious With Parkland At Your Door.
Exuding contemporary style, outstanding quality and a peaceful position in trendy Pentridge Village, embrace a carefree lifestyle on the footsteps of parkland with this excellent tri-level townhouse.
With scenic Coburg Lake, Brosnan Community Park, Coburg Olympic Swimming Pool and the Merri Creek Trail only a short stroll (or jog) away, it's a location that's perfect for fitness enthusiasts, and when you consider the close proximity of a childcare centre, schools, Coburg Market and Sydney Road trams, shops and cafes, it's a smart lifestyle choice for a host of buyers.
Crafted with a smart low maintenance design, this move-straight-into residence instantly appeals with its soaring three-storey façade and introduces a radiant open-plan living area on the first-floor, where stainless steel appliances and stone benchtops add style and substance to the modern kitchen and sliding doors integrate the fashionable interior with the undercover balcony hello cocktails at sunset!
All three bedrooms and a bright main bathroom are zoned on the upper level to offer a superior level of privacy and comfort; the master bedroom enjoying the luxury of its own ensuite and large walk-in robe.
Featuring a remote double garage with internal access, separate laundry, powder room and split-system cooling and central heating, make your move!

Description:
Character, Space And Convenience
With a wealth of period details and city conveniences close by, this freestanding two bedroom single fronted timber block façade Victorian home makes for an enchanting lifestyle opportunity. A traditional layout, of central lounge, dining room and hallway, features leadlight aspects, high ceilings and open fireplaces with mirrored timber surrounds. While an extension adds modern functionality and houses main bathroom, laundry/storage and light filled kitchen/meals opening onto a covered alfresco deck and leafy garden. A well equipped kitchen displays stainless steel cooking appliances, dishwasher, modern benches and cabinetry. There are two double bedrooms, one has an open fireplace, while the other boasts a built-in-robe. Enhanced by gas log fire, split-system and automated garage. On a corner near shops, cafés, markets and public transport.
Currently leased until 2nd October 2018 for $1977 per month.

Description:
Exceptional Space & Endless Options
Coburg's most amazing multi-level residence to come onto the market, delivers a unique environment of absolute quality and floorplan flexibility alongside stunning views. The ground floor showcases a large rumpus room with double remote control garage and plenty of storage space. Step up the stairs to the second floor or take your own private lift (servicing all floors) to a large living area, private theatre room and beautiful dining area with multiple balconies, served by an expansive open plan kitchen featuring Electrolux appliances. The third level contains three bedrooms each with a private balcony and built in robes, whilst the master suite features a full ensuite and walk in robe. The top level features another bedroom which showcases built in robes plus an ensuite, separate living area revealing front and rear balconies ideal for entertaining and enjoying the spectacular views on offer. This outstanding package is made complete by its central position only moments to Coburg Train Station, Nicholson Street / Sydney Road Tram lines, Coburg Secondary College, shops, cafes and Coburg Lake.
All buyers must register to attend the inspections by emailing the agent with contact name, phone number & email. Photo I.D will also be required upon entry.

Description:
Captivating Californian Bungalow In Coburg's Heart
Evoking incredible period charm, this heritage rich four bedroom, two bathroom Californian Bungalow is set on approximately 480sqm amidst magnificent gardens. Opening to a rarely seen octagonal hallway, graced with ornate timber fretwork, high ceilings, deep cornices and polished Baltic pine floorboards, the home is certain to leave a lasting impression. A leadlight entry, elegant lounge, offering fourth bedroom potential, and charming living/dining zone, featuring triple-paned original glass aspect, provide sophisticated spaces for relaxing and entertaining. Adding appeal, established manicured gardens offer privacy and superb alfresco dining and entertaining options. Towards the rear an immaculate kitchen/meals, displaying stainless steel upright cooker, dishwasher and ample storage/benches, enjoys a blissful garden outlook. Impeccable accommodation is provided by robed bedrooms, including one with an oversized walk-in-robe. The main boasts generous built-in-robes and designer ensuite. Features period inspired bathroom, ducted heating, split-system, alarm, mature fruit trees and extra-large automated double garage/workshop/storage via ROW. Only moments to vibrant cafes, shopping strips, schools, parklands and public transport.
Insights: 120 Barrow Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 49 other 4 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Corner The Future You Want
Featuring spacious, open design and a corner position within a stroll of popular Melville Road, this single storey three bedroom residence is ready to entice a range of buyers. Along with a very generous living room and flowing open kitchen, dining and family domain there's a largely paved courtyard with space to dine alfresco and a front garden filled with roses. Timber cabinetry, great counter space, a gas cooktop, fan forced oven and rangehood fill the practical kitchen with everything needed to whip up delicious meals. Three double bedrooms with built-in robes, a dual entry bathroom, bay windows, ducted heating, split system heating and cooling and an automatic garage confirm appeal. With St Fidelis Primary over the road and Coburg West Primary a stroll away, it's also a short walk to trams, parks, cafes and local shops, and a quick drive can take you to CityLink access and have you in the CBD in next to no time.
